attributes.title: The Fun-Raiser
attributes.caption: When the funding for the camp runs out, David and Gwen have to come up with a way to save Camp Campbell from closing. So they steal the Quatermaster's hook hand and task the campers with comping up with fundraiser ideas to replace it.
attributes.description: When the funding for the camp runs out, David and Gwen have to come up with a way to save Camp Campbell from closing. So they steal the Quatermaster's hook hand and task the campers with comping up with fundraiser ideas to replace it.

attributes.title: Ered Gets Her Cool Back
attributes.caption: An uncool blunder has left Ered questioning her identity, so she tries to make up for it with a dangerous stunt with help from Nerris. Meanwhile, the other campers try out to be the new "coolest camper."
attributes.description: An uncool blunder has left Ered questioning her identity, so she tries to make up for it with a dangerous stunt with help from Nerris. Meanwhile, the other campers try out to be the new "coolest camper."

attributes.title: Foreign Exchange Campers
attributes.caption: Camp Campbell is visited by some foreign exchange campers, but something seems... off about some of them. What are they hiding? Why are they so interested in Cameron Campbell? Suspicious...
attributes.description: Camp Campbell is visited by some foreign exchange campers, but something seems... off about some of them. What are they hiding? Why are they so interested in Cameron Campbell? Suspicious...

attributes.title: Nikki's Last Day on Earth
attributes.caption: After drinking an experimental tonic of Neil's creation, Nikki is suddenly not feeling well and is diagnosed with a case of Death. How will Nikki spend her last day alive?
attributes.description: After drinking an experimental tonic of Neil's creation, Nikki is suddenly not feeling well and is diagnosed with a case of Death. How will Nikki spend her last day alive?
attributes.display_title: S3:E4 - Nikki's Last Day on Earth

attributes.title: Dial M For Jasper
attributes.caption: David is visited by the vision of an old friend. Max, Neil, and Nikki do some sleuthing to find out why David is so shaken up by the whole thing.
attributes.description: David is visited by the vision of an old friend. Max, Neil, and Nikki do some sleuthing to find out why David is so shaken up by the whole thing.

attributes.title: The Lake Lilac Summer Social
attributes.caption: The annual lake-wide dance is not going well, mainly because everyone attending hates one another. But when Neil starts crushing on Erin from the Flower Scouts, Gwen tries to play matchmaker between them, only to have it backfire horribly.

attributes.title: Cameron Campbell the Camp Campbell Camper
attributes.caption: Cameron Campbell has reappeared at the camp! Or rather, the new camper "Samboy Kidwell" sure looks like him anyway. He sure is acting funny -- almost like he has an ulterior motive or something?

attributes.title: Something Fishy
attributes.caption: At a run-down summer camp in the 2010s, a lonely camp counselor forms a unique relationship with an amphibious creature that has emerged from the lake.
attributes.description: At a run-down summer camp in the 2010s, a lonely camp counselor forms a unique relationship with an amphibious creature that has emerged from the lake.

attributes.title: The Candy Kingpin
attributes.caption: Max forms an underground candy mafia after discovering Dolph has a huge box of sugary treats. Dolph wants a friendship instead of a business partnership, but Max is more interested in having power than a friend.
attributes.description: Max forms an underground candy mafia after discovering Dolph has a huge box of sugary treats. Dolph wants a friendship instead of a business partnership, but Max is more interested in having power than a friend.

attributes.title: Operation: Charlie Tango Foxtrot
attributes.caption: The Wood Scouts take turns telling the tale of how they executed their latest and most ambitious plan to take over Camp Campbell to date.
attributes.description: The Wood Scouts take turns telling the tale of how they executed their latest and most ambitious plan to take over Camp Campbell to date.

attributes.title: City Survival
attributes.caption: Gwen and David need to go into the big city and are bringing the kids with them. When Max decides to show Neil and Nikki all the fun things the city has to offer, he breaks away from the group and it's up to David to track them down.

attributes.title: Camp Corp.
attributes.caption: With Camp Campbell sold off due to lack of funds, the campers are split up and sent off to the camps they intended to sign up for. Max is left alone, and with a decision to make.

attributes.title: Arrival of the Torso Takers
attributes.caption: After watching a spooky horror video, Max becomes increasingly concerned with David's behavior.
attributes.description: After watching a spooky horror video, Max becomes increasingly concerned with David's behavior. Is Max just overreacting, or is there actually something wrong with David?
attributes.display_title: S3:E13 - Arrival of the Torso Takers

attributes.title: Culture Day
attributes.caption: It's Culture Day at Camp Campbell, and the kids find themselves drawn to Neil's Jewish ancestry. Neil gets carried away with the story of Hanukkah. Meanwhile, David tries to get everything ready for the big Culture Day feast!
